<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Documentation</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400">Step-by-step guide to integrating ExtPay Manager with your extensions.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-12 prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">1. Setup Flutterwave</h3>
            <p>Create a Flutterwave account and get your API keys from the <b>Settings > API Keys</b> section. You'll need the Public Key, Secret Key, and you should define a Secret Hash for webhooks.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">2. Add your Extension</h3>
            <p>Go to the <a href="/extensions" class="text-blue-400">Extensions</a> page and add your extension. The <b>slug</b> is important as it identifies your extension in API calls.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">3. Create Pricing Plans</h3>
            <p>For each extension, create one or more pricing plans. You can choose between One-Time, Monthly, or Yearly payments.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">4. AI Integration Prompt (Cursor/VS Code)</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Copy this prompt and paste it into your AI IDE (like Cursor or VS Code with Copilot) to automatically integrate the payment system into your extension or website.</p>
            
            <div class="relative group">
                <pre class="bg-slate-950 p-6 rounded-2xl text-sm border border-slate-800 text-blue-300 whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>I want to integrate a payment and license system into my Chrome Extension. 
I am using ExtPay Manager located at: <%= appUrl %>

Please perform the following:
1. In the extension background script, implement a `verifyLicense(licenseKey)` function that POSTs to `<%= appUrl %>/api/verify` with the `licenseKey` and extension slug.
2. Create a UI in the extension popup for users to enter their license key and save it to `chrome.storage.local`.
3. On my website, create a "Buy" button that calls `<%= appUrl %>/pay/init` with the `planId` and user's email, then redirects to the returned Flutterwave link.

The extension slug is: [YOUR_EXTENSION_SLUG]
The plan IDs are: [YOUR_PLAN_IDS]</code></pre>
                <button class="absolute top-4 right-4 bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs transition-all" onclick="copyToClipboard(this)">Copy Prompt</button>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">5. Sample Website</h3>
            <p>We've created a sample website for you in the <code>/sample-website</code> folder of this project. You can use it as a template for your own landing page.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h4 class="text-blue-400 font-bold mb-2">Pro Tip: Webhooks</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Always configure the webhook URL in Flutterwave. This ensures that even if a user's internet drops after payment, the license will still be generated and the user will receive it via email (if you implement email sending) or can be found in your dashboard.</p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    function copyToClipboard(btn) {
        const code = btn.previousElementSibling.innerText;
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(code).then(() => {
            const originalText = btn.innerText;
            btn.innerText = 'Copied!';
            setTimeout(() => btn.innerText = originalText, 2000);
        });
    }
</script>
